text.tspan: Positive protection devices may be used per Section 6M.02.
This TTC zone application may be used as an alternate to the TTC application shown in Figure 6P-10
(using faggers) when the following conditions exist:
Vehicular traffc volume is such that suffcient gaps exist for vehicular traffc that must yield.
b. Road users from both directions are able to see approaching vehicular traffc through and beyond the
worksite and have suffcient visibility of approaching vehicles.
The Type B fashing warning lights may be placed on the ROAD WORK AHEAD and the ONE LANE
ROAD AHEAD signs whenever a night lane closure is necessary.
Notes: See Table 6P-2 for the meanings of
the symbols used in this figure.
See Table 6B-1 for the meanings of
the letter codes used in this figure.
